-- European Stocks Advance as Repsol Shares Rally on Brazil; Cap Gemini Gains
-- B y   D a v i d   M e r r i t t
-- 2010-10-01T11:05:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-01/european-stocks-erase-gains-as-santander-bnp-paribas-drop-repsol-rallies.html
European stocks erased an earlier
rally as shares in the regions banks fell. U.S. futures pared
their advance and Asian shares gained.  The benchmark Stoxx Europe 600 Index fell 0.1 percent to
259.35 at 12:02 p.m. in London. Banco Santander SA, Spain’s
largest lender, fell 1.3 percent, while BNP Paribas, France’s
biggest bank, lost 2 percent. Repsol YPF SA surged 5.8 percent
as Sinopec pledged to invest $7.1 billion in its Brazilian unit.  Futures on the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index rose 0.3
percent, trimming a 0.7 percent rise, and the MSCI Asia Pacific
Index gained 0.6 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Merritt at 
 dmerritt1@bloomberg.net  